==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*sūz'' ‘sow’, from Indo-European ''*suHs'' ‘pig’.

''Germanic cognates:'' Old Saxon [[su#Old Saxon|sū]], Old High German [[su#Old High German|sū]] (German [[Sau]]), Old Norse [[sýr]] (Swedish [[so#Swedish|so]]).

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[ὗς]], Latin [[sus|sūs]], Old Church Slavonic [[свинъ]] (Russian [[свиной]]), Old Irish [[socc]], Tocharian B ''suwo''.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /su:/

===Noun===
'''sū'''
# a [[sow]]

===Related words===
*[[sugu]]

